{"search_data": "Central PM Ujjwala Yojana for Free LPG Connections to BPL Women to be Launched on May 1stWith a budget outlay of Rs. 8000 crores, 5 Crore LPG connections will be provided to the BPL households. The scheme will run over three years in 2016-17, 2017-18, and 2018-19. In the years 2016-17 alone, there is a target of providing free LPG connections to 1.5 Crore BPL households with a budgetary provision of Rs. 2000 Crores.Under the PM Ujjwala Yojana, government will provide a financial assistance of Rs. 1600 for LPG connection to each household. The amount will be directly credited into the bank accounts of the eligible beneficiaries.The scheme will ensure women empowerment and their health protection along with the reduction in time spent on cooking. The scheme will also benefit rural youth in providing employment in supply chain of cooking gas.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}